    <item>
      <title>Easy and fast dust removal in Digikam&#43;Gimp</title>
      <link>http://brunettoziosi.eu/posts/easy-and-fast-dust-removal-in-digikamgimp/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 04 Sep 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://brunettoziosi.eu/posts/easy-and-fast-dust-removal-in-digikamgimp/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s a long time I was searching for an easy and fast way to remove dust spot from my photos.&lt;br /&gt;
Unfortunately it seem that until now no tools like &amp;ldquo;dust removal mask&amp;rdquo; or something similar are present in the open-source/linux panorama.&lt;br /&gt;
But yesterday I&amp;rsquo;ve found a &lt;a href=&#34;http://dodonov.net/blog/2009/12/29/cleaning-dust-on-photos-or-in-gimp-we-trust/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;post&lt;/a&gt; explaining how to use a Gimp plugin to easy clean photos from dust spot.&lt;br /&gt;
It was not exactly what I was searching for but it worked really well.&lt;br /&gt;
The only thing to to it was to find a way to automatize the task.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After some thinking I&amp;rsquo;ve found this way:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In Digikam, right-click on the photo and select &amp;ldquo;Open in Gimp&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In Gimp:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add a new transparent layer (reduce opacity to see the photo&amp;rsquo;s layer)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paint on the spots with the brush (this will be our &amp;ldquo;mask&amp;rdquo;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the layer window select the new layer and click on &amp;ldquo;Alpha to selection&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the layer window selectthe photo&amp;rsquo;s layer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ctrl+x to remove dust spot&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Selection-&amp;gt;Grow selection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Filters-&amp;gt;Map-&amp;gt;Resynthetize&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Save with postfix &amp;ldquo;_v1&amp;rdquo; (non destructive editing supported in Digikam)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy you photo:)



&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

